<section class="fl-section fl-problem" id="problem">
  <div class="fl-container">
    <div class="fl-problem__grid fl-reveal">
      <div class="fl-problem__text">
        <div class="fl-label fl-problem__label">{{ section.settings.label }}</div>
        <h2 class="fl-problem__headline">{{ section.settings.headline }}</h2>
        <div class="fl-problem__body">{{ section.settings.body }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fl-problem__visual">
        <img
          src="{{ section.settings.image | default: 'commerce-broken-dark.png' | asset_url }}"
          alt="Broken vendor stack vs unified platform"
          loading="lazy"
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Problem Section",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "label",
      "label": "Label",
      "default": "The Problem"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "headline",
      "label": "Headline",
      "default": "The problem isn't one thing. It's everything not connecting."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "body",
      "label": "Body",
      "default": "<p>You know what this feels like. The payment processor doesn't talk to the commission engine. Attribution breaks and the wrong rep gets credit. A sync drops and suddenly commissions are wrong. A promo code doesn't fire because two systems have conflicting data.</p><p>Your team spends its week keeping this Frankenstein alive.</p><p>Your reps — the people your entire model depends on — quietly stop trusting the system. They share a link, someone else gets credit, and they learn a hard lesson: using the corporate platform is a risk. So they stop.</p><p>When reps stop sharing, traffic dies. When traffic dies, growth stalls. The technology was supposed to help. Instead it became the obstacle.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "image",
      "label": "Illustration"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
